1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:03,240
I bow to all the seekers of truth.

2
00:00:07,360 --> 00:00:18,610
As I told you before, that the Spirit has the nature of being the truth itself,

3
00:00:19,990 --> 00:00:23,650
and this truth is the love of God.

4
00:00:25,500 --> 00:00:39,270
So the truth is, that God is love, that this power that works in you is love.

5
00:00:40,960 --> 00:00:48,530
Love of God, and love of God is pure love.

6
00:00:49,900 --> 00:00:54,460
We have lost the sense of purity because of our own venturesomeness,

7
00:00:55,810 --> 00:01:00,680
but purity is where the love has no lust, no greed.

8
00:01:00,810 --> 00:01:02,590
It is innocent.

9
00:01:05,660 --> 00:01:09,260
Like the sap in the tree rises,

10
00:01:10,510 --> 00:01:15,480
nourishes the whole tree and goes back; it does not get attached to any

11
00:01:15,560 --> 00:01:21,270
particular flower or to any particular leaf and says that,

12
00:01:21,410 --> 00:01:25,810
“I like this.” It is absolutely detached.

13
00:01:27,790 --> 00:01:38,880
It just nourishes and goes back, but carnal love is like the sap rises,

14
00:01:39,240 --> 00:01:46,940
goes into a flower and gets lost; thus the flower will also die, the tree will

15
00:01:47,020 --> 00:01:57,630
also die, and one must understand that when you get after Realization,

16
00:01:57,710 --> 00:02:07,550
what you have to do is first of all to see yourself, how much you love others.

17
00:02:10,520 --> 00:02:15,810
How much your heart has opened for love.

18
00:02:16,850 --> 00:02:18,690
How much you can share.

19
00:02:19,820 --> 00:02:23,000
The individualism should drop out.

20
00:02:23,230 --> 00:02:25,430
That is collective consciousness.

21
00:02:26,880 --> 00:02:34,310
It does not mean that you can feel the chakras of another person.

22
00:02:34,390 --> 00:02:35,630
You can feel the chakras that you have the problems.

23
00:02:35,710 --> 00:02:37,410
You go on like that.

24
00:02:37,490 --> 00:02:44,700
It means that when the Spirit starts shining in your attention,

25
00:02:44,880 --> 00:02:52,550
first thing that you develop a great compassion for this human race.

26
00:02:53,290 --> 00:02:58,460
Not for the animals or for the bugs like the many vegetarians do,

27
00:02:58,540 --> 00:03:01,000
but for the human beings.

28
00:03:01,080 --> 00:03:03,380
They are the epitome of evolution.

29
00:03:06,450 --> 00:03:12,180
So you develop your love for other human beings

30
00:03:12,260 --> 00:03:17,800
because they become part and parcel of your being.

31
00:03:17,880 --> 00:03:24,640
Now for example, a finger is sick and the other finger looks after it.

32
00:03:26,490 --> 00:03:31,120
It is not doing any obligation, but actually it is soothing because

33
00:03:31,200 --> 00:03:38,040
if this is soothed, all the body comes to a very pleasant state.

34
00:03:38,120 --> 00:03:45,800
If this is unpleasant, the whole body is in an unpleasant state.

35
00:03:46,794 --> 00:03:51,500
So if you treat one finger, you are treating the whole.

36
00:03:51,580 --> 00:04:00,000
In the same way, your compassion starts flowing, but many people have very funny

37
00:04:00,080 --> 00:04:06,820
ideas about compassion also and these must be corrected through experimentation.

38
00:04:08,160 --> 00:04:14,020
Some of the ideas of compassion are that you should worry all

39
00:04:14,100 --> 00:04:18,820
the time about people who are absolutely at the low ebb of life.

40
00:04:20,290 --> 00:04:24,250
As a Mother I would say, you have to first mature yourself.

41
00:04:25,660 --> 00:04:30,100
As children you are still growing, that is what humility means.

42
00:04:30,260 --> 00:04:35,080
Understand that you have to still become the Spirit in the full way,

43
00:04:35,160 --> 00:04:39,770
and just now to jump to tasks of taking

44
00:04:39,850 --> 00:04:44,050
up very difficult cases will be very dangerous and you

45
00:04:44,130 --> 00:04:48,990
may get enwrapped into it and your progress may stop.

46
00:04:49,070 --> 00:04:52,720
So as humble students of Sahaja Yoga,

47
00:04:53,120 --> 00:05:01,870
first you have to learn how to master it yourself, to become

48
00:05:01,950 --> 00:05:05,016
a person who does not catch from other people,

49
00:05:07,617 --> 00:05:11,590
who does not get troubles from other people.

50
00:05:11,670 --> 00:05:15,970
In a way, such a person has to be very cautious.

51
00:05:19,120 --> 00:05:21,560
Now I have seen so many people.

52
00:05:23,307 --> 00:05:25,040
They come to the programs,

53
00:05:25,120 --> 00:05:29,080
they find one person who is possessed, shouting, screaming,

54
00:05:30,920 --> 00:05:36,320
and a Sahaja Yogi who is really matured will say, “Now you get out of this place,

55
00:05:36,400 --> 00:05:39,100
you should not be here,” because that person

56
00:05:39,180 --> 00:05:41,860
will know that everybody will be troubled

57
00:05:41,940 --> 00:05:46,350
by this person, because this person has got a disease which will be contagious.

58
00:05:46,430 --> 00:05:51,590
All mental troubles are contagious which people do not know, like psychologists.

59
00:05:51,670 --> 00:05:54,510
They do not know that they are treating psychopaths.

60
00:05:54,590 --> 00:05:56,630
They themselves become psychopaths,

61
00:05:56,710 --> 00:05:59,794
because they have no way of protecting themselves.

62
00:05:59,874 --> 00:06:04,740
So first of all you must protect yourself and you find anybody like that,

63
00:06:05,040 --> 00:06:07,860
better not go near that person.

64
00:06:07,940 --> 00:06:12,680
At the most you can say, “Mother, look after this man,” if you have

65
00:06:12,760 --> 00:06:17,420
so much of feelings, but sympathy of this kind is very dangerous.

66
00:06:17,500 --> 00:06:20,840
I call it ‘symp’ means to share and ‘pathy’ means pathos.

67
00:06:20,920 --> 00:06:25,420
So you share the pathos of a madman and you get into troubles.

68
00:06:25,500 --> 00:06:32,160
So as good children I have to warn you that you should get more attached,

69
00:06:33,410 --> 00:06:41,220
more adhered to a person who is more evolved, more enlightened.

70
00:06:41,660 --> 00:06:46,120
Instead of that, people start feeling jealous and get ego-oriented

71
00:06:46,880 --> 00:06:51,420
and start fighting with a person who is much better off.

72
00:06:52,080 --> 00:06:59,860
Now Dr. Warren, as you know, has achieved it, a very great height in Sahaja Yoga,

73
00:07:00,600 --> 00:07:06,890
but in Australia, I found many people who were really jealous of him

74
00:07:06,970 --> 00:07:12,840
for nothing at all and they wanted to oust him, while they themselves were at

75
00:07:12,920 --> 00:07:17,554
the low ebb and they always wanted to go to people who are at a lower ebb.

76
00:07:17,634 --> 00:07:19,300
If you have to go higher,

77
00:07:19,380 --> 00:07:23,620
then you have to stick on to people who have gone little higher and

78
00:07:23,700 --> 00:07:27,220
not to go to such people who are at a lower ebb,

79
00:07:27,300 --> 00:07:30,920
while they can come up only by looking up.

80
00:07:31,150 --> 00:07:34,770
So you cannot bring them by going down to them.

81
00:07:34,850 --> 00:07:39,190
So those people who have got Realization for the first time, who have just touched

82
00:07:39,270 --> 00:07:41,550
it, should not suddenly start thinking:

83
00:07:41,630 --> 00:07:46,560
now they have become the great evolved people.

84
00:07:46,640 --> 00:07:55,080
They have to grow – grow like trees and acquire the knowledge of their powers.

85
00:07:55,160 --> 00:07:59,500
For example, if I entered into one room, that does not mean that I have gone to

86
00:07:59,580 --> 00:08:04,600
all the rooms, that does not mean that I know what is happening in other rooms.

87
00:08:04,680 --> 00:08:10,380
So for a person who has got Realization, has to be humble about it;

88
00:08:10,460 --> 00:08:14,880
that, I have to see more and I have to know more, I have to be better.

89
00:08:14,960 --> 00:08:18,530
This attitude helps a lot in their growth,

90
00:08:18,610 --> 00:08:25,420
and once you have achieved the higher state, which we call as Nirvikalpa, means

91
00:08:25,500 --> 00:08:36,280
doubtless awareness, after that you yourself can start with great enthusiasm,

92
00:08:36,360 --> 00:08:41,120
helping people, those who are much lower than you.

93
00:08:42,049 --> 00:08:45,610
This is one of the reasons many people who come to

94
00:08:45,690 --> 00:08:49,290
Sahaja Yoga go down and take lot of time to come up.

95
00:08:50,110 --> 00:08:51,710
Sahaja Yoga is becoming.

96
00:08:52,337 --> 00:08:56,270
It is not that you can make somebody a plastic Sahaja Yogi.

97
00:08:56,350 --> 00:08:59,150
You cannot give a certificate, “All right,

98
00:08:59,270 --> 00:09:05,310
now you are a realized soul.” It is you who has to certify yourself.

99
00:09:05,390 --> 00:09:11,330
It is you who has to grow up and it is you who has to master it.

100
00:09:11,760 --> 00:09:16,060
It is you who knows whether you have got it or not.

101
00:09:16,150 --> 00:09:21,690
So you have to have due respect for yourself and for others.

102
00:09:22,430 --> 00:09:26,230
The second problem arises that a person becomes bumptious

103
00:09:28,140 --> 00:09:31,740
and starts quarrelling with Sahaja Yogis, taking sides

104
00:09:31,820 --> 00:09:36,780
of people who are negative, people who are not yet anywhere

105
00:09:36,860 --> 00:09:40,460
– is also a common sight I have seen with many people.

106
00:09:41,200 --> 00:09:44,540
So one should see, “What changes have come in me,

107
00:09:45,224 --> 00:09:49,490
what transformation has taken place in me?” One can even write a

108
00:09:49,570 --> 00:09:52,770
diary to see, “Have I become more compassionate,

109
00:09:53,130 --> 00:09:58,080
have I become more tolerant, have I become much more nourishing?

110
00:09:58,160 --> 00:10:01,120
Can I share things with others?

111
00:10:01,560 --> 00:10:07,050
Do I enjoy the company of others and the company of Sahaja

112
00:10:07,130 --> 00:10:11,110
Yogis?” But that does not mean that you have to enjoy

113
00:10:11,190 --> 00:10:15,690
the company of the people who are not realized and not

114
00:10:15,770 --> 00:10:19,640
to enjoy the company of the people who are realized.

115
00:10:19,720 --> 00:10:24,100
In India we have very good saints and very realized souls,

116
00:10:24,180 --> 00:10:29,480
and their idea about human beings is very sad, because

117
00:10:29,560 --> 00:10:36,240
they think that human beings can never understand that when they have to grow up,

118
00:10:36,540 --> 00:10:38,900
they have to grow up with humility.

119
00:10:38,980 --> 00:10:43,513
Like a student has to learn from a professor, you have to learn from

120
00:10:44,160 --> 00:10:49,400
your Kundalini how to grow, how to become better by watching yourself.

121
00:10:50,780 --> 00:10:54,860
They think that unless and until the guru is very strict,

122
00:10:54,940 --> 00:10:58,220
actually, like the gurus you have in the market, they are not.

123
00:10:58,300 --> 00:11:00,580
They are very different type of people.

124
00:11:00,660 --> 00:11:03,220
They are terribly hard task masters.

125
00:11:03,394 --> 00:11:08,860
If you see, their methods are so horrifying that I shudder to send anyone to them.

126
00:11:09,314 --> 00:11:12,780
Once I had sent one gentleman, he had told Me,

127
00:11:12,860 --> 00:11:19,040
there was one guru called as Gagangad Maharaj, who is a real guru, and he is very

128
00:11:19,120 --> 00:11:24,200
well known, but he lives in the jungles and his legs are broken

129
00:11:24,280 --> 00:11:28,920
and hands are broken by human beings, and he is carried by a tiger.

130
00:11:30,427 --> 00:11:34,160
So he told Me, “Mother, if you, if anybody troubles you,

131
00:11:34,240 --> 00:11:35,480
if you are in difficulties with

132
00:11:35,560 --> 00:11:40,990
somebody who is very troublesome, you send him over to me.” So I said, “All right.”

133
00:11:41,070 --> 00:11:45,250
The one gentleman who was very torturesome, he used to ask questions

134
00:11:45,330 --> 00:11:49,120
after questions like mad and very troublesome fellow, very ego-oriented.

135
00:11:49,200 --> 00:11:54,140
So just I said, “All right, you go and see this guru.” Now this

136
00:11:54,220 --> 00:11:56,900
guru does not see people at all, so he felt very enamoured.

137
00:11:56,980 --> 00:12:00,160
His ego was pampered, “Oh God, the guru has called me,

138
00:12:00,240 --> 00:12:02,240
something great.” So he went to that guru.

139
00:12:02,320 --> 00:12:07,870
After a month he came back, and like there was a big passage,

140
00:12:08,030 --> 00:12:15,440
and his legs were on his neck, and they were ringing him, as if dangling towards Me.

141
00:12:15,520 --> 00:12:16,760
I looked at him.

142
00:12:17,034 --> 00:12:20,300
I could not bear it, and tears came into my eyes.

143
00:12:20,380 --> 00:12:23,210
I said, “What has happened to him?” He said, “Mother,

144
00:12:23,290 --> 00:12:27,940
I am sorry for what I did.” I said, “What happened?” He said, “You see,

145
00:12:28,020 --> 00:12:34,480
when I went there, I was rather bad because I told against you to the guru.” I said,

146
00:12:34,560 --> 00:12:35,800
“What did you tell against the guru?”

147
00:12:35,880 --> 00:12:40,700
He said: “I told that Mother is giving Realization to every Tom,

148
00:12:40,780 --> 00:12:44,160
Dick and Harry, and She should really first of all verify and

149
00:12:44,240 --> 00:12:49,130
then give Realization and this and that, and I was talking ill about you.” He said,

150
00:12:49,210 --> 00:12:52,150
“Yes, you are wiser than Mother, isn’t it?

151
00:12:52,230 --> 00:12:59,700
And then in the night the tiger came and threw me in a ‘khud’ and fell down,

152
00:12:59,780 --> 00:13:02,200
fourteen feet down.

153
00:13:02,280 --> 00:13:13,720
And then this guru lowered some bread after three days and asked that,

154
00:13:15,960 --> 00:13:21,990
“You can eat this food but stay there.” And I was lying there for five days.”

155
00:13:22,250 --> 00:13:31,390
And every day he (guru) used to lower the bread for him and he was there,

156
00:13:31,894 --> 00:13:34,360
all filled with filth and everything.

157
00:13:35,060 --> 00:13:39,260
After five, six days he sent three, four people to pick him up,

158
00:13:40,480 --> 00:13:46,040
and when he came up, he asked them to give him a bath and all that and a change.

159
00:13:46,200 --> 00:13:48,520
And then he told that,

160
00:13:48,600 --> 00:13:53,640
“You put these legs around your neck and go dangling to Mother.

161
00:13:53,720 --> 00:13:56,340
She is the one who will put you right, not me,

162
00:13:56,420 --> 00:13:58,700
and if you ever say a word against Mother,

163
00:13:58,780 --> 00:14:05,840
then I will break your legs in such a way that you will never be able to fix them.”

164
00:14:05,920 --> 00:14:10,270
Poor fellow, he was shattered, and he came to Me, “Mother,

165
00:14:10,350 --> 00:14:12,430
it was too much.” Of course, his legs were fixed.

166
00:14:12,510 --> 00:14:13,490
He is all right.

167
00:14:13,570 --> 00:14:19,250
He is a good fellow now, but that is what they do, because according to them,

168
00:14:19,330 --> 00:14:23,090
unless and until you take them to task, you cannot humble them down.

169
00:14:23,170 --> 00:14:24,390
Like another fellow.

170
00:14:24,470 --> 00:14:30,020
I sent him to another fellow who was a doctor and who used to really

171
00:14:30,100 --> 00:14:33,920
bother Me too much, but I just told him, go and see this particular guru.

172
00:14:34,000 --> 00:14:37,240
So when the doctor came back, he was thin like sticks.

173
00:14:37,320 --> 00:14:38,580
I said, what has happened?

174
00:14:38,660 --> 00:14:43,290
Didn’t he not give you food to eat? “No Mother, he gave me food all right,

175
00:14:43,370 --> 00:14:46,870
he was very affectionate.” But what happened, why did you lose so much weight?

176
00:14:46,950 --> 00:14:48,150
What has happened to you?

177
00:14:48,230 --> 00:14:49,830
You are looking so very thin.

178
00:14:49,910 --> 00:14:56,290
So he was staying about seven miles, one had to walk up, and every day he

179
00:14:56,370 --> 00:15:02,430
had to carry two buckets of water to clean one dilapidated temple there.

180
00:15:02,510 --> 00:15:05,920
Every day he was supposed to take that and clean it.

181
00:15:06,000 --> 00:15:10,900
So I asked this guru, “What do you mean by torturing him like this, taking these

182
00:15:10,980 --> 00:15:15,960
two buckets to clean the thing?” He said, “For a donkey you must give donkey’s work.

183
00:15:16,040 --> 00:15:19,540
I am not a Mother to look after these ego-oriented people.

184
00:15:19,620 --> 00:15:23,486
It is better that he is trash now, he will be better off.”

185
00:15:23,670 --> 00:15:27,950
So this is what, the way they think people can be taught and

186
00:15:28,030 --> 00:15:32,110
they are to learn their lessons of spirituality in this way.

187
00:15:32,190 --> 00:15:38,490
Even when you go to them, they will test you in so many ways that you absolutely get

188
00:15:39,384 --> 00:15:44,850
fed up and you leave them and they are very happy that you have left them forever.

189
00:15:44,930 --> 00:15:47,410
They are never anxious that you should be close to

190
00:15:47,490 --> 00:15:50,250
them because it is a thankless job, otherwise if

191
00:15:50,330 --> 00:15:52,800
you see, if you do not take any money,

192
00:15:52,880 --> 00:15:56,460
you are never rewarded, people try to always boss over you.

193
00:15:56,540 --> 00:15:59,700
So they think that: it is better first to put them right,

194
00:15:59,780 --> 00:16:05,440
let them learn that you have to go hard way to be the Spirit.

195
00:16:05,880 --> 00:16:08,740
But Sahaja Yoga today is not like that.

196
00:16:09,240 --> 00:16:13,040
As a Mother I thought, let these children who are already

197
00:16:13,120 --> 00:16:16,620
under pressure and tension receive their Realization.

198
00:16:16,700 --> 00:16:18,580
Let them have their Realization.

199
00:16:18,660 --> 00:16:23,034
Let them have their light again and let them see what is wrong with them.

200
00:16:23,114 --> 00:16:27,580
Then they start seeing their ego, they start seeing their superego,

201
00:16:27,660 --> 00:16:31,100
they start seeing their conditionings, they start seeing

202
00:16:31,180 --> 00:16:35,200
their problems and gradually when they see it, they can cleanse it,

203
00:16:35,280 --> 00:16:38,970
if you tell them how to cleanse it and they work it out.

204
00:16:39,050 --> 00:16:44,230
So after Realization, it is very important how you look after yourself.

205
00:16:44,310 --> 00:16:49,170
You may be a king, you may be anything, makes no difference.

206
00:16:49,250 --> 00:16:53,150
In the realm of God, the one who is an evolved soul is respected.

207
00:16:53,230 --> 00:17:00,190
Not the person who just is a big man or something, a big politician, has no place.

208
00:17:00,270 --> 00:17:03,330
Only thing is who is more evolved.

209
00:17:03,460 --> 00:17:09,999
Even a simple person on the street can come to Sahaja Yoga and can rise very high,

210
00:17:10,079 --> 00:17:12,279
and a person who comes in a big car

211
00:17:12,359 --> 00:17:18,499
and a big way and tries to all the time impress upon Me the

212
00:17:18,579 --> 00:17:23,040
greatness of his worldly treasures, does not reach anywhere.

213
00:17:23,704 --> 00:17:27,970
So in the eyes of God, it is not important what you are in life,

214
00:17:28,050 --> 00:17:32,970
what your ego tells you, what you think of yourself, but it is God’s

215
00:17:33,050 --> 00:17:36,930
judgment that He sees how far you are in Realization,

216
00:17:37,010 --> 00:17:42,750
and in Realization you have to judge yourself through your vibratory awareness.

217
00:17:42,830 --> 00:17:48,980
When this awareness stations down properly and you really become absolutely

218
00:17:49,060 --> 00:17:55,920
endowed with it, the joy of Sahaja Yoga starts trickling in your existence.

219
00:17:56,000 --> 00:17:57,200
People can see you.

220
00:17:57,280 --> 00:18:04,350
Those who never laughed, started laughing aloud, feeling the joy of life.

221
00:18:04,430 --> 00:18:08,190
The whole drama becomes sometimes a comedy,

222
00:18:08,270 --> 00:18:12,130
sometimes a tragedy and you start seeing the whole drama

223
00:18:12,210 --> 00:18:15,750
as a witness, and when this happens, then a person really,

224
00:18:15,830 --> 00:18:20,430
really enjoys the beauty of their Spirit.

225
00:18:20,510 --> 00:18:23,730
But those who think that they are great and

226
00:18:23,810 --> 00:18:26,510
they have read this book and they have been to

227
00:18:26,590 --> 00:18:28,910
this guru or they have done this great job,

228
00:18:28,990 --> 00:18:32,610
they must know that it is not counted at all.

229
00:18:32,690 --> 00:18:38,990
It is how you are within yourself, where are your vibrations and what

230
00:18:39,070 --> 00:18:43,770
are the chakras you have opened out, how much large you have grown.

231
00:18:43,850 --> 00:18:47,310
That is how a person is known by his evolution.

232
00:18:47,390 --> 00:18:49,590
You are all seekers of ages.

